header.gameNote: PHILLIPS 66 BIG 12 WOMEN'S CHAMPIONSHIP - QUARTERFINAL AT KANSAS CITY MO

article.description: Alexia Standish scored 25 points, including 6 of 9 on 3-pointers, and No. 22 Texas A&M pulled away late in the second half to handle Kansas 78-63 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Alexia Standish leads A&M over Kansas
article.linkText: Standish, No. 14 Texas A&M handle Kansas
article.story:
KANSAS CITY, Mo. --  Alexia Standish scored 25 points, including 6 of 9 on 3-pointers, and No. 14 Texas A&M pulled away late in the second half to handle Kansas 78-63 on Thursday night, advancing to the Big 12 women's championship semifinal.

The Aggies scored 11 unanswered points that concluded with 3:24 remaining to transform an eight-point advantage into a 73-54 cushion. Kansas would get no closer than 15 for the remainder of the game.

Kansas sliced an eight-point deficit to 52-49 with 12:10 remaining on a layup by Aishah Sutherland, but Texas A&M countered with six straight points. The Jayhawks remained within striking distance until the Aggies went on an 11-0 run six minutes later.

Sydney Carter scored 18 points and Kelsey Bone added 16 for the Aggies; both players also had seven rebounds apiece.

Angel Goodrich led Kansas with 21 points and nine assists.
